<worksheet label="ws-act-8a-1-1">
  <activity xml:id="act-8a-1-1">
    <introduction>
      <p>
        Let <m>f(x)=e^x</m> and <m>T_2(x) = b_0 + b_1 x + b_2 x^2</m>.  We seek numerical values for the constants <m>b_0</m>, <m>b_1</m>, and <m>b_2</m> so that <m>f(0)=T_2(0)</m>, <m>f'(0)=T_2'(0)</m>, and <m>f''(0)=T_2''(0)</m>.
      </p>
    </introduction>
    <task workspace="3cm" xml:id="act-8a-1-1-task-0">
      <statement>
        <p>
					Note that since <m>b_0</m>, <m>b_1</m>, and <m>b_2</m> are constants, if we take the derivative of the quadratic function <m>T_2</m> using the sum and constant multiple rules, it follows that <m>T_2'(x) = b_1 + 2 b_2 x</m>.   
				</p>
        <p>
					What is <m>T_2''(x)</m>?
				</p>
      </statement>
      <hint/>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>T_2''(x) = 2b_2</m>.
				</p>
      </answer>
      <solution>
        <p>
          <m>T_2''(x) = 2b_2</m>.
				</p>
      </solution>
    </task>
